    "Name": "Scimitar HCV",
    "Details": "Based on the TAG variant, this version replaces all the weapons with a Rotary AC/2 with 2 tons of ammunition and a C3 slave. It also increases protection by carrying Heavy Ferro-Fibrous armor. The Scimitar Medium Hover Tank is very similar to the Saracen. Following the success of that combat vehicle, Scarborough Limited designed another pair of tanks with the same chassis to capitalize on sales. Their plan was successful, and Scarborough had another hit on their hands, five years after the release of the Saracen.\n\n<b><color=#ffcc00>Biome Restrictions: This unit can not deploy in Lunar or Martian biomes due to using an ICE.</color></b>\n\n<b><color=#ffcc00>Movement: 8/12 hexes / 240/360 meters.</color></b>\n\n<color=#ffcc00><b>Armor:</b> Heavy Ferro-Fibrous\n<b>Structure:</b> Structure\n<b>Values       A        S  </b>\n<b>Front</b>       210     20\n<b>Left</b>         140     20\n<b>Right</b>       140     20\n<b>Rear</b>        100     20\n<b>Turret</b>      155     20\n\n<b>Total</b>      745    100</color>\n\n<color=#ff0000>Quirk: Rugged</color>",
